* the prepared text in our textpart-per-line format with dotted ref
* can be multiple *.txt files but, if there is an inherent order to the files, this should be reflected in the sort order of the filenames

The Greek text narrative portion of Chambers' reader is composed of 48 sections broken up into "parts" of twelve chapters each. The dot format hierarchy used is `Part.Section.Paragraph.Line`. Zero-values in dot notation indicate headings. 